\left|\,a-b+c-c\,\right|=\left|\,(c-a)+(c-b)\,\right|,
\left|\,a-b+c-c\,\right| = \left|\,(a-c)+(c-b)\, \right|?
a = b = 1; c = 2
|(2-1) + (2-1)| = |2| = 2
a - b + c - c = (a-c) + (b-c)
|a-b+c-c| \neq |(c-a)+(c-b)|
a=0, b=10, c=5
|a-b+c-c| = |a+(-b)+c+(-c)| = |(a+(-c))+(c+(-b))| = |(a-c)+(c-b)|
a\ne c
